Central European countries are very literate. All of them have the literacy rate of 96% or over (for both sexes):
Languages.
Languages taught as the first language in Central Europe are: German, Polish, Romanian, Czech, Hungarian, Serbian, Slovenian, Croatian, Slovak, and Lëtzebuergesch. The most popular language taught at schools in Central Europe as foreign languages are: English, French and German.
